Chief Great Ovedje Ogboru, the APC governorship candidate in Delta State and his party, on Tuesday, closed their case with presentation of documented evidence at the  election petitions tribunal sitting in Asaba. Ogboru and APC, after calling about 20 witnesses, decided to close their case. Ogboru is challenging the re-election of Governor Ifeanyi Okowa of PDP as winner of the March 9 election. Apart from calling witnesses, the petitioners also tendered volumes of documentary evidence which included voters’ registers and results from polling units’ level to the state level as proof of their case. Meanwhile, the 1st respondent, Okowa, who was supposed to open his defence, yesterday, pleaded for time to enable him study the case of the petitioners. Notwithstanding the application, the tribunal insisted that his time started running from yesterday, July 17. Delta: Ogboru, APC closes case, Okowa, begins defence July 23 Rivers election: Wike opens defence at tribunal …As Okowa urges opponents to sheath sword Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin